# fc2123869aca4317b8650bfaf0806a62
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:41
msgid ""
":func:`TSHttpParserCreate` creates an HTTP parser object. The parser's "
"data structure contains information about the header being parsed. A "
"single HTTP parser can be used multiple times, though not simultaneously."
" Before being used again, the parser must be cleared by calling "
":func:`TSHttpParserClear`."
msgstr ""

# 58fb27ac62f940e58e1dbe9d0a218d69
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:47
msgid ""
":func:`TSHttpHdrParseReq` parses an HTTP request header. The HTTP header "
":arg:`offset` must already be created, and must reside inside the marshal"
" buffer :arg:`bufp`. The :arg:`start` argument points to the current "
"position of the string buffer being parsed and the :arg:`end` argument "
"points to one byte after the end of the buffer to be parsed. On return, "
":arg:`start` is modified to point past the last character parsed."
msgstr ""

# 2fc3a1b3693a4403afc57df2d34ae835
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:55
msgid ""
"It is possible to parse an HTTP request header a single byte at a time "
"using repeated calls to :func:`TSHttpHdrParseReq`. As long as an error "
"does not occur, the :func:`TSHttpHdrParseReq` function will consume that "
"single byte and ask for more. :func:`TSHttpHdrParseReq` should be called "
"after :data:`TS_HTTP_READ_REQUEST_HDR_HOOK`."
msgstr ""

# 3afdc42a4e5f4a9b8a59b099dbf810ff
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:61
msgid ""
":func:`TSHttpHdrParseResp` operates in the same manner as "
":func:`TSHttpHdrParseReq` except it parses an HTTP response header. It "
"should be called after :data:`TS_HTTP_READ_RESPONSE_HDR_HOOK`."
msgstr ""

# 44c6799e7e9941fabf4492d192a98b3b
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:65
msgid ""
":func:`TSHttpParserClear` clears the specified HTTP parser so it may be "
"used again."
msgstr ""

# 11b09e9f206b479e84123f3ed3cc7a7b
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:68
msgid ""
":func:`TSHttpParserDestroy` destroys the TSHttpParser object pointed to "
"by :arg:`parser`. The :arg:`parser` pointer must not be NULL."
msgstr ""

# 2fefce3e68ba49a99cf1a0ca501aa409
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:72
msgid "Return Salues"
msgstr ""

# 401d2ac89ff14809bcbc935c947ec569
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:74
msgid ""
":func:`TSHttpHdrParseReq` and :func:`TSHttpHdrParseResp` both return a "
":type:`TSParseResult` value. :data:`TS_PARSE_ERROR` is returned on error,"
" :data:`TS_PARSE_CONT` is returned if parsing of the header stopped "
"because the end of the buffer was reached, and :data:`TS_PARSE_DONE` or "
":data:`TS_PARSE_OK` when a \\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n pattern is encountered, "
"indicating the end of the header."
msgstr ""

# f3709e95590343eca302efe2d7b5486c
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:82
msgid "Known Bugs"
msgstr ""

# 8f9c2baf7694447fa45f3d6c13e353c0
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSHttpParserCreate.en.rst:84
msgid ""
"The distinction between the :data:`TS_PARSE_DONE` and :data:`TS_PARSE_OK`"
" results is not well-defined. Plugins should expect both status codes and"
" treat them equivalently."
msgstr ""

